      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOCKDOWN (2) stalked the lead from a middle box before hitting the front turning and lifting to score (24.91) at this track in a Grade 3/4 over 450m. Has good speed and a low draw is a big help. Looks the one to beat. RED REIGN (6) made an eye-catching debut when rocketed out of the boxes with a fast early sectional, clocking 22.24 in a 2.5 lengths win at this track over 400m. Promising type and rates a leading chance again. CESSNOCK CURTAIN (1) missed the frame last time at Wentworth Park but was a Grade 4/5 winner the start prior (24.88) and goes well this journey. Good beginner and aided by the inside draw. Has the ability and can find best this time. BRAILEY BANNER (5) is always hard to beat when he races here at this trip.",
